OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,419,410,140,120,000,100
PN,41805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1783720151
OL,3,CMosque effigy on Moygashel bonfire
OL,4,C'sickening and cowardly'
OL,6,F"He remains in custody at this time."
OL,8,FThe DUP said effigies should not be
OL,9,Fplaced on bonfires.
OL,11,FUlster Unionist Party Leader, Jon
OL,12,FBurrows has called for the "immediate
OL,13,Fremoval of the offensive display".
OL,15,FFermanagh and South Tyrone Sinn Fein
OL,16,FMLA Colm Gildernew described the
OL,17,Fdisplay on the bonfire as "deplorable".
OL,19,FAlliance Party councillor Eddie Roofe
OL,20,Fdescribed the bonfire as "hateful and
OL,21,Fdeeply offensive".
